This paper deals with decoding of error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which are commonly used in network coding and communication systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm involves trellis-based check node processing, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing and communication systems (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the complexity of the algorithm, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents simulation results for nonbinary LDPC codes, which is a topic in coding theory and error-correcting codes (cs.CC).
